caption: I go to this restaurant often! This is my favorite restaurant to have a bite.  I go to this spot many times. The food is very tasty, the team is polite and the prices are affordable. I like meeting in this restaurant over a decent dinner.
The food is constantly fresh and yummy, employees hands out awesome customer service. I really like the cleanliness and mood. Keep up the good work.

The best Thai ever! Thai tea- perfect not too sweet! Green curry- spicy and eggplant is tender and delish. Amazing dinner special. Coming again tomorrow night with more friends. My only complaint..... I live in Idaho and I'm not closer!

Great and simple place. Everyone was really kind an helpful. Ambience is very relaxed.  I order roasted duck and stir fried veggies with garlic rice.  Food was exceptional. I'll be coming back for sure.  If you are ever looking for fast easy comforting Thai food, joom is where to go!

Tasty Asian bowl spot offering a spin on the classic bibimbap.  Base options include white rice, brown rice and noodles, while toppings include shredded egg, bean sprouts but also quinoa and cucumber.  I’d recommend the steak in terms of protein, though vegetarian options are also available.

Great variety of fresh toppings, charismatic staff (Just met Reo and he's well-spoken, engaging, and incredibly helpful). Totally coming back!

BIBIBOP offers quick Korean food from a simple menu. The bibimbap is pretty good, and there is a nice variety of vegetable sides and sauce options. The protein portion is a bit small, but I personally like that it's not just a bowl of meat. Value is good, too -- especially if you get the small bowl that has the same amount of protein.

Great place! Good vibes.This is fusion place, so just keep that in mind and enjoy the food (aka don't expect it to be "authentic Korean," that's not the point).  Some plentiful portions (I would say even more than Chipotle) and you can get a pretty healthy meal out of it (or really make it as you want it!).
Chipotle idea applied to Korean bibimbap.  Tasty but wish they would give more meat.  Sauces can be kind of salty if you combine them but I'd recommend the yum yum sauce.
